        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/salt505/{size}/8288_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-26T15:11:53.690Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong>Problem:</strong> Both iPhone users and Android users can use the desktop client, but the desktop client only displays emoji in the style of iOS.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Solution 1:</strong> In Signal Desktop preferences, add an option that would allow the user to select what kind of emoji they want displayed in messages.<br>\nThe user could choose between the following emoji styles:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>iOS - matches the style of emoji found on <a href=\"https://emojipedia.org/apple/\">Apple devices</a></li>\n<li>Android (Google) - matches the style of emoji by <a href=\"https://emojipedia.org/google/\">Google</a>, found on most Android devices</li>\n<li>System - respects the default system emoji found on whatever device is being used (MacOS/Windows/Linux)**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>**This option couldn‚Äôt be the default because some desktops might not have proper emoji built in</p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Solution 2:</strong> (Thanks to <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/awaitlink\">@awaitlink</a>)<br>\nApparently there are different styles of the Desktop client that change based on the type of parent device (Android or iOS). Signal could simply utilize this same behavior to also change the emoji type to match that of the parent device.</p>\n</blockquote>",
