      {
        "id": 66042,
        "name": "Salt",
        "username": "Salt505",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/salt505/{size}/8288_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-26T15:29:53.939Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators quote-modified\" data-username=\"awaitlink\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"14477\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/awaitlink/48/48975_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> awaitlink:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There are already two different styles of the Desktop app (that depend on the master device): Android and iOS. AFAIK they only affect message bubble coloring at the moment. I imagine it would make sense to change the emoji font based on that?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>That would be a great way to do it! I don‚Äôt think this would be <em>too</em> much of a hassle to implement then.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"awaitlink\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"14477\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/awaitlink/48/48975_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> awaitlink:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You could use <a href=\"https://emojipedia.org/google/\">Google‚Äôs emojis</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>You‚Äôre right, I fixed that in the main post, thanks!</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"awaitlink\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"14477\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/awaitlink/48/48975_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> awaitlink:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>However that still wouldn‚Äôt satisfy everyone I think.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Nothing ever will, unfortunately.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators quote-modified\" data-username=\"awaitlink\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"14477\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/awaitlink/48/48975_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> awaitlink:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>different emoji sets sometimes assign different meaning to the same emoji.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>You know, I understand what you‚Äôre saying here, but I don‚Äôt really think that happens as much anymore. Sure, this was a big issue back in the day, but these days most emoji are almost identical apart from tiny art differences.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"awaitlink\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"14477\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/awaitlink/48/48975_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> awaitlink:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Linux has to be taken into account as well. At the very least this ‚Äúsystem‚Äù option shouldn‚Äôt be the default IMO, as that can lead to confused users (see point 2 below).</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This is true, maybe that option could be hidden on Linux.</p>",
