        "name": "",
        "username": "Leptopoda",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/leptopoda/{size}/5476_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-01-26T23:08:20.691Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Also just adding to the discussion that many android devices use different emojis. I‚Äôve heard that Samsung is the de facto standard android manufacturer in the us and I can confirm this with some other countries. Asia in the meanwhile have a lot of OPPO, Xiaomi or Huawei (and their subsidiaries).</p>\n<p>It would probably be quite difficult to implement this the proper way. Just using the google one isn‚Äôt a solution either.</p>\n<p>Also keep in mind that the iOS style has been the standard on android forever and thus the people affected by this change would probably be the minority.</p>",
