        "username": "Cromefire",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/cromefire/{size}/28599_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-02-17T20:04:19.012Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"Leptopoda\" data-post=\"11\" data-topic=\"14477\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/leptopoda/48/5476_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Leptopoda:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Also just adding to the discussion that many android devices use different emojis. I‚Äôve heard that Samsung is the de facto standard android manufacturer in the us and I can confirm this with some other countries. Asia in the meanwhile have a lot of OPPO, Xiaomi or Huawei (and their subsidiaries).</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Well from a technical standpoint it‚Äôs only really possible (without major restructuring) to have ios, android/google, twitter and facebook (incomplete) emotes right now (due to the use of <code>emoji-datasource</code> and no system emotes aren‚Äôt possible with the current implementation which is not saying it‚Äôs impossible at all, just way harder), so I guess it would be at least better to have 2 very different styles of emotes for now than to have no choice at all (once 2 are implemented it would be really easy to add the other 2, but it‚Äôs adding to the app size and I‚Äôm not sure if it‚Äôs worth it).</p>\n<p>I‚Äôm also happy to assist with the implementation of this feature, but I‚Äôm not quite certain, how to get the setting working, the rest shouldn‚Äôt be a problem.</p>\n<p>I started the implementation here: <a href=\"https://github.com/cromefire/Signal-Desktop/tree/google-emotes\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">GitHub - cromefire/Signal-Desktop at google-emotes</a> I‚Äôm still debating though whether I want to provide literally all of my data via the CLA, so it may not get merged (or even proposed for merge), feel free to get a patch of it tough and start your own PR.</p>",
